description:
The Great Irish Bake Off - Series 3, Episode 8




Grand Final

Anna Nolan presents the grand final of the baking contest. The last demanding challenges are to prepare three floating deconstructed apple crumbles that can be served in a martini glass and a three-tiered wedding cake with a love theme. Paul Kelly and Lilly Higgins pass judgement on their efforts, while the nine eliminated contestants return to lend moral support.




Original Air Date: 13-Dec-2015
